1
00:00:00,370 --> 00:00:01,770
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,770 --> 00:00:03,440
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,440 --> 00:00:05,240
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:07,080 --> 00:00:08,080
(Episode 37)

5
00:00:11,720 --> 00:00:13,590
Double the lobbying funds?

6
00:00:14,390 --> 00:00:16,020
Double, as in 40 million dollars?

7
00:00:26,870 --> 00:00:28,030
That must be the politician...

8
00:00:28,030 --> 00:00:29,400
Chairman Park was going
to make a deal with.

9
00:00:31,040 --> 00:00:33,300
I thought their deal was over.

10
00:00:35,970 --> 00:00:37,780
The deal needs to fall through...

11
00:00:38,080 --> 00:00:39,780
so he thinks
it's Choi Yu Na's fault,

12
00:00:40,380 --> 00:00:42,610
and that'll make him go after her.

13
00:00:46,790 --> 00:00:49,090
Chairman Park won't give up
on this deal.

14
00:00:49,790 --> 00:00:51,820
If the lobbying funds keep growing,

15
00:00:52,490 --> 00:00:55,660
he'll have to dip
into his slush fund.

16
00:00:56,730 --> 00:01:00,430
Then you'll finally find out
where he keeps his money.

17
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:04,400
You'll get a chance to find
the slush fund ledgers or evidence.

18
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:06,200
Exactly.

19
00:01:06,840 --> 00:01:09,040
This deal can't fall through
completely.

20
00:01:10,010 --> 00:01:11,640
I'm going to keep
raising the stakes...

21
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:15,150
and use it as a trap
to catch Park Tae Ho.

22
00:01:19,120 --> 00:01:21,450
Assemblyman Kwon, please forgive
the humble accommodations.

23
00:01:22,620 --> 00:01:23,620
After you.

24
00:01:38,070 --> 00:01:41,670
Yes. We can put a complete stop
to Chairman Park's deal.

25
00:01:42,870 --> 00:01:44,410
Now that I have photo evidence,

26
00:01:44,810 --> 00:01:47,410
release the article we prepared
immediately.

27
00:01:49,350 --> 00:01:50,920
What article are you referring to?

28
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:14,010
An article about our exclusive
development rights deal?

29
00:02:14,510 --> 00:02:15,840
How did a story like that get out?

30
00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:27,520
(Chairman Park Tae Ho's
lobbying scandal)

31
00:02:27,590 --> 00:02:29,790
(Park Tae Ho of Adele Group Accused
of Lobbying for Overseas Deals)

32
00:02:34,830 --> 00:02:38,000
This must be the story you mentioned
outside the chairman's office.

33
00:02:40,100 --> 00:02:42,130
Chloe, did you release that article
about the chairman...

34
00:02:42,670 --> 00:02:44,670
- and Assemblyman Kwon?
- No.

35
00:02:45,140 --> 00:02:48,910
- It was Ms. Choi.
- Chloe.

36
00:02:48,910 --> 00:02:50,640
I thought I made myself
perfectly clear.

37
00:02:51,640 --> 00:02:53,180
Whatever I'm doing,

38
00:02:54,550 --> 00:02:55,880
stay out of it.

39
00:02:58,120 --> 00:03:00,750
That's the only way
I'll stay quiet about your secret,

40
00:03:01,190 --> 00:03:02,920
that you were the one...

41
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:06,060
who tipped off the police
about the false appraisal.

42
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:09,430
Don't think you have leverage
over me...

43
00:03:09,430 --> 00:03:11,660
when all you've got is suspicion.

44
00:03:14,770 --> 00:03:16,300
If you try to make this public...

45
00:03:17,300 --> 00:03:18,600
with those photos you just took,

46
00:03:18,970 --> 00:03:21,440
I'll expose your secret first.

47
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:27,510
I can also frame you as the source
behind the false appraisal report.

48
00:03:28,910 --> 00:03:30,050
You'd be wise...

49
00:03:31,150 --> 00:03:32,480
to heed my warning.

50
00:03:34,320 --> 00:03:36,150
Isn't this what you wanted?

51
00:03:37,260 --> 00:03:40,190
Why else would you tip off
the police about yourself?

52
00:03:41,030 --> 00:03:43,060
Didn't you want to kill this deal?

53
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:45,360
So you have no reason
to get in my way.

54
00:03:45,700 --> 00:03:48,370
Sorry, but you've got it all wrong.

55
00:03:49,630 --> 00:03:51,000
What I want...

56
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:53,910
is for no one else
to get involved in this.

57
00:03:55,470 --> 00:03:58,140
Keep your personal vendetta
out of it.

58
00:04:13,160 --> 00:04:14,190
A personal vendetta?

59
00:04:15,660 --> 00:04:17,100
You have no idea.

60
00:04:32,110 --> 00:04:34,410
Is this what you call
doing your job?

61
00:04:35,910 --> 00:04:40,180
Get out there and fix this mess.
Get all the articles taken down!

62
00:04:41,090 --> 00:04:42,090
Yes, sir.

63
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:46,120
(Chairman Park Tae Ho)

64
00:04:47,160 --> 00:04:49,330
Did the deal fall through
because of the article?

65
00:04:49,730 --> 00:04:52,160
Assemblyman Kwon stormed out
before I could explain.

66
00:04:53,030 --> 00:04:54,970
The development rights deal
and the lobbying are all...

67
00:04:54,970 --> 00:04:56,270
out in the open now.

68
00:04:57,070 --> 00:05:00,070
I even offered to double the money
to keep him on board,

69
00:05:01,140 --> 00:05:02,270
but he still chose to play it safe.

70
00:05:02,910 --> 00:05:05,210
But it's not completely
off the table yet.

71
00:05:05,210 --> 00:05:08,110
Considering how he ran,
I wouldn't bet on it.

72
00:05:08,110 --> 00:05:10,250
Darn.

73
00:05:11,350 --> 00:05:13,580
I almost had him.

74
00:05:15,390 --> 00:05:17,690
Who could've leaked this?

75
00:05:22,430 --> 00:05:26,060
That darn Choi Yu Na.
She's got some nerve.

76
00:05:26,660 --> 00:05:29,930
(Chairman Park Tae Ho)

77
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:34,110
We can't be sure it was Ms. Choi.

78
00:05:35,540 --> 00:05:36,540
Then who else?

79
00:05:37,340 --> 00:05:40,180
Who else knows about the lobbying
to leak this?

80
00:05:41,410 --> 00:05:43,310
Of the people who saw
the lobbying files,

81
00:05:43,780 --> 00:05:46,550
the only one reckless enough
is Ms. Choi.

82
00:05:47,190 --> 00:05:48,820
It had to be her.

83
00:05:50,660 --> 00:05:53,360
If Chloe keeps trying
to frame Ms. Choi,

84
00:05:53,760 --> 00:05:55,990
it could interfere with my plan.

85
00:06:00,930 --> 00:06:03,470
James, I don't think
we can run a follow-up story.

86
00:06:04,270 --> 00:06:06,600
President Kim is getting in the way
of our plan.

87
00:06:07,510 --> 00:06:10,070
I'll find another way to do this
without releasing the article.

88
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:20,950
What if we move up the competition
between Ms. Choi and Chloe?

89
00:06:21,420 --> 00:06:23,020
They won't be able
to get in your way...

90
00:06:23,020 --> 00:06:24,790
if they're focused
on the competition.

91
00:06:25,290 --> 00:06:27,930
Yes, I was thinking just that.

92
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:32,260
Here. Take this.

93
00:06:33,870 --> 00:06:35,770
I've already put together
a task for them.

94
00:06:36,030 --> 00:06:38,540
Tell them both to get started
right away.

95
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:42,440
Before I can get big things done,

96
00:06:43,510 --> 00:06:46,540
I need to tie up these loose ends.

97
00:06:58,620 --> 00:07:00,630
Don't tell me
you released the article.

98
00:07:02,060 --> 00:07:03,060
What article?

99
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:05,100
The chairman's deal
with Assemblyman Kwon.

100
00:07:05,630 --> 00:07:06,860
You knew about it too.

101
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:09,570
Even if I knew,
I'd have no reason to leak it.

102
00:07:10,130 --> 00:07:13,240
Whether the deal goes through or not
has nothing to do with me.

103
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:18,640
If anything, I'd suspect you,
Ms. Choi.

104
00:07:19,280 --> 00:07:20,910
You might've tried
to backstab him...

105
00:07:21,210 --> 00:07:22,950
out of frustration
about having to compete.

106
00:07:24,780 --> 00:07:27,490
I even had the photos
on my phone deleted.

107
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:30,050
Besides, he suspects
I reported the fake appraisal.

108
00:07:30,050 --> 00:07:31,390
So why would I be so reckless?

109
00:07:31,790 --> 00:07:32,790
If you say so.

110
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:46,770
The chairman gave you both a mission
to compete for.

111
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:07,630
Wait, shouldn't you be heading back
to the office?

112
00:08:08,190 --> 00:08:11,630
That article is causing a huge mess.
Shouldn't you be doing something?

113
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:14,630
That's exactly what she'd expect.

114
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:18,840
While that sly Kim Myung Hui
is distracted with damage control,

115
00:08:18,900 --> 00:08:21,440
we need to blindside her.

116
00:08:22,670 --> 00:08:25,810
What will it take to make
that vicious witch cry?

117
00:08:26,010 --> 00:08:30,250
You know what they say.
Hurt someone, and you'll cry blood.

118
00:08:31,050 --> 00:08:33,950
Just let it go,
for "our" Hyun Jun's sake.

119
00:08:35,920 --> 00:08:37,420
Why are you calling him that again?

120
00:08:37,590 --> 00:08:39,820
Why bring him up at all?

121
00:08:43,730 --> 00:08:47,030
No matter how vicious that woman is,
a mother is still a mother.

122
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:51,700
The best way to hurt her is
to hurt her child.

123
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:52,800
What?

124
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:57,540
I told you to let it go.
Why are you making things worse?

125
00:09:06,450 --> 00:09:07,950
My father gave you an assignment?

126
00:09:08,350 --> 00:09:09,350
Yes.

127
00:09:14,090 --> 00:09:15,130
Who's this?

128
00:09:15,260 --> 00:09:17,300
You know the "Health is Science"
series, right?

129
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:20,930
It's a famous health documentary
that's on TV and streaming services.

130
00:09:21,170 --> 00:09:24,600
He's the producer of the series
and CEO of the production company.

131
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:32,410
(Adele Group Bio Launch:
Global OTT Promotion Plan)

132
00:09:32,780 --> 00:09:37,180
The mission is to get our product
featured on the show's next season.

133
00:09:38,350 --> 00:09:41,120
I'm a designer,
not part of the bio team.

134
00:09:41,190 --> 00:09:42,520
This is totally unfair.

135
00:09:44,490 --> 00:09:45,790
You have to help me.

136
00:09:47,190 --> 00:09:48,190
Please?

137
00:09:49,530 --> 00:09:51,930
I have no intention of marrying you,

138
00:09:52,160 --> 00:09:54,970
and I want you out
of this company more than anyone.

139
00:09:55,770 --> 00:09:56,770
So why would I help you?

140
00:09:58,770 --> 00:09:59,770
Would you rather...

141
00:09:59,770 --> 00:10:02,470
just watch Chloe win
and marry Hyun Jun?

142
00:10:02,770 --> 00:10:06,580
Or will you star in some sordid
love triangle between brothers?

143
00:10:07,510 --> 00:10:09,650
Actually, that role
would suit Chloe perfectly.

144
00:10:10,010 --> 00:10:12,850
A homewrecker bouncing
between two brothers.

145
00:10:15,950 --> 00:10:17,490
Watch your mouth.

146
00:10:18,860 --> 00:10:20,730
You can't avoid choosing,
either way.

147
00:10:21,190 --> 00:10:23,830
Marry me and ruin her wedding,

148
00:10:23,830 --> 00:10:26,630
or watch her get married
and have your own heart broken.

149
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:29,930
One or the other will happen,
whether you like it or not.

150
00:10:32,670 --> 00:10:34,740
There's a third option,
and that's destroying you.

151
00:10:36,770 --> 00:10:38,180
If you drag me into this,

152
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:41,810
I'll destroy you first.

153
00:10:46,980 --> 00:10:47,990
Fine.

154
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:49,550
Whatever.

155
00:10:50,760 --> 00:10:52,820
I'll win this without your help.

156
00:10:53,990 --> 00:10:55,030
Just you watch.

157
00:11:06,570 --> 00:11:08,240
An unavoidable choice?

158
00:11:16,780 --> 00:11:20,080
I'll need to make a proposal
to persuade him.

159
00:11:20,550 --> 00:11:22,920
If I can show him
how strong our bio division is,

160
00:11:23,450 --> 00:11:24,890
I think I've got a shot.

161
00:11:26,060 --> 00:11:27,830
Let's work on it together.
I can help.

162
00:11:28,690 --> 00:11:29,760
I'd like to do it on my own.

163
00:11:30,900 --> 00:11:33,430
I want to win this on my own merit.

164
00:11:36,400 --> 00:11:40,600
Okay.
Let me know if you need my help.

165
00:11:47,680 --> 00:11:48,680
(BIT Life, President Kim Myung Hui)

166
00:11:54,390 --> 00:11:56,650
Is the issue with the article
being addressed?

167
00:11:57,290 --> 00:11:59,860
And no follow-up articles
or damaging photos have surfaced?

168
00:11:59,860 --> 00:12:02,960
Yes, I think Chloe listened to you
and backed off.

169
00:12:03,030 --> 00:12:06,160
Keep an eye on things, just in case
anything else comes up.

170
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:07,500
Got it.

171
00:12:08,430 --> 00:12:11,800
What if Assemblyman Kwon backs out
of the deal because of this?

172
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:15,140
Our plan was to raise the stakes
and use him.

173
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:18,510
Would offering him more money
change his mind?

174
00:12:19,180 --> 00:12:21,310
He was already offered double.

175
00:12:21,710 --> 00:12:23,680
To go higher than that,

176
00:12:24,150 --> 00:12:26,280
Chairman Park will have
to make a tough call.

177
00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:27,690
That's true.

178
00:12:27,990 --> 00:12:31,660
Even for Chairman Park,
paying eight figures isn't easy.

179
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:35,490
But given the amount and the timing,
this was the perfect opportunity.

180
00:12:36,160 --> 00:12:38,630
I didn't expect Chloe
to get in the way like this.

181
00:12:38,860 --> 00:12:41,970
You're still going to help Chloe
with the competition, right?

182
00:12:42,700 --> 00:12:46,140
It's better if Chloe wins
than Ms. Choi.

183
00:12:56,210 --> 00:12:57,210
What the...

184
00:12:57,980 --> 00:12:59,380
- For crying out loud.
- What?

185
00:13:00,780 --> 00:13:02,290
What on earth?

186
00:13:03,690 --> 00:13:06,460
What is it this time?

187
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:09,160
From the way you look,

188
00:13:09,190 --> 00:13:11,200
it doesn't seem
like you got thrown out.

189
00:13:11,330 --> 00:13:13,300
We're here about the wedding.

190
00:13:13,700 --> 00:13:14,700
What?

191
00:13:15,330 --> 00:13:16,900
- Again?
- Again?

192
00:13:19,970 --> 00:13:23,470
A marriage between our daughter
and Director Park Min Jun...

193
00:13:23,740 --> 00:13:25,540
was arranged.

194
00:13:25,610 --> 00:13:29,850
Look, we have no intention
of becoming your in-laws,

195
00:13:29,910 --> 00:13:31,350
so get lost.

196
00:13:31,350 --> 00:13:33,650
No, that's not why we're here today.

197
00:13:34,080 --> 00:13:36,190
This isn't about asking
for her hand in marriage.

198
00:13:37,690 --> 00:13:38,760
We're here to help you
with her situation.

199
00:13:39,160 --> 00:13:41,190
You're willing to help her
get married to Min Jun?

200
00:13:41,190 --> 00:13:43,090
Wait. Why would you?

201
00:13:44,900 --> 00:13:47,770
It seems you haven't heard
about the chairman's little contest.

202
00:13:48,370 --> 00:13:49,400
What?

203
00:13:54,470 --> 00:13:56,470
What are you doing here?

204
00:13:57,810 --> 00:14:01,310
You. Can you beat that Chloe girl?

205
00:14:01,950 --> 00:14:04,350
It doesn't matter if you can or not.

206
00:14:04,350 --> 00:14:06,650
You have to win
and marry Park Min Jun.

207
00:14:18,860 --> 00:14:20,160
(Adele Group Bio Launch:
Global OTT Promotion Plan)

208
00:14:22,430 --> 00:14:24,940
So all I have to do
is sweet-talk one person?

209
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:27,470
Why are you offering to help me?

210
00:14:28,070 --> 00:14:29,540
Are you after
my family's shares again?

211
00:14:30,610 --> 00:14:33,380
I'm after something more important
than a few shares.

212
00:14:34,580 --> 00:14:35,650
Something more important?

213
00:14:35,680 --> 00:14:37,250
My pride.

214
00:14:38,650 --> 00:14:40,950
If you marry that punk Park Min Jun,

215
00:14:41,190 --> 00:14:43,890
just imagine how livid
Kim Myung Hui will be.

216
00:14:44,190 --> 00:14:47,560
Plus, Chloe will get kicked out
of Adele.

217
00:14:47,930 --> 00:14:50,160
Think how satisfying
that will be for me.

218
00:14:50,430 --> 00:14:52,300
You're using my marriage
to benefit yourself?

219
00:14:52,500 --> 00:14:55,030
Just take what you can get
while you have the chance.

220
00:14:55,370 --> 00:14:56,770
Won't both your marriage...

221
00:14:57,030 --> 00:14:59,170
and your career at Adele be over
if you fail?

222
00:15:02,740 --> 00:15:05,740
Fine. Just look into
that producer for me.

223
00:15:06,140 --> 00:15:08,310
Start with his weaknesses.

224
00:15:12,180 --> 00:15:14,490
There you go,
ordering me around again.

225
00:15:14,850 --> 00:15:18,620
Just because I said I'd help you
doesn't mean you can boss me around.

226
00:15:19,190 --> 00:15:22,330
On this one, I'm calling the shots.

227
00:15:23,630 --> 00:15:27,330
You don't have anything on me,
so I won't be your puppet.

228
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:29,730
Let's just say
we're using each other...

229
00:15:29,730 --> 00:15:31,270
out of mutual necessity.

230
00:15:44,650 --> 00:15:47,850
I know they're a rich
and powerful family,

231
00:15:48,390 --> 00:15:50,190
but a competition
where marriage is the prize?

232
00:15:50,990 --> 00:15:52,460
Isn't that going too far?

233
00:15:53,190 --> 00:15:54,260
That's Chairman Park for you.

234
00:15:56,830 --> 00:15:59,260
The chairman has always been
like that.

235
00:15:59,730 --> 00:16:04,500
He pits his wives against each other
and is always testing his two sons.

236
00:16:04,740 --> 00:16:06,640
So why would his daughters-in-law
be any different?

237
00:16:08,470 --> 00:16:09,470
Is that so?

238
00:16:10,270 --> 00:16:11,840
Never mind all that.

239
00:16:12,440 --> 00:16:15,250
At the end of the day,
she has to win, right?

240
00:16:16,210 --> 00:16:20,180
But I don't know if we can trust
the chairman's wife again.

241
00:16:21,320 --> 00:16:23,020
Would you stop for a second?

242
00:16:23,490 --> 00:16:25,590
Is she really on our side this time?

243
00:16:25,760 --> 00:16:29,060
She did say she came to help.

244
00:16:38,270 --> 00:16:39,940
I should get going.

245
00:16:40,300 --> 00:16:41,310
- What?
- What?

246
00:16:41,770 --> 00:16:44,240
- What the... Hold on!
- What...

247
00:16:44,340 --> 00:16:46,210
Is she helping us or not?

248
00:16:46,280 --> 00:16:48,650
What's going on?
Where are you going?

249
00:16:49,410 --> 00:16:50,410
Hey!

250
00:16:51,550 --> 00:16:53,220
What was that? Good grief.

251
00:17:01,160 --> 00:17:03,560
Please find out everything you can
about Producer Shin.

252
00:17:04,630 --> 00:17:06,030
You'll get on that right away,
won't you?

253
00:17:06,430 --> 00:17:09,130
What? Well, that's...

254
00:17:09,330 --> 00:17:11,240
Even with my mother's objections,

255
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:14,070
I can't give up on this marriage,

256
00:17:14,140 --> 00:17:15,840
so I have to win the competition.

257
00:17:16,910 --> 00:17:17,910
Mr. Song.

258
00:17:18,840 --> 00:17:20,280
You'll take my side...

259
00:17:21,010 --> 00:17:22,080
and help me, right?

260
00:17:23,380 --> 00:17:24,720
By your side, Hyun Jun?

261
00:17:27,180 --> 00:17:31,420
Should I value Jung Ran's pride
or Hyun Jun's love?

262
00:17:32,820 --> 00:17:33,890
Well, of course...

263
00:17:34,190 --> 00:17:37,460
Of course I'm on your side.

264
00:17:37,730 --> 00:17:40,060
I'll help you protect
your relationship with her,

265
00:17:40,130 --> 00:17:41,200
so don't you worry.

266
00:17:43,570 --> 00:17:46,000
I'll go look into it right now.
Okay?

267
00:17:55,510 --> 00:17:56,610
Baek Jin Ju.

268
00:17:58,580 --> 00:18:00,550
I don't know what you're planning,

269
00:18:02,250 --> 00:18:03,250
but our wedding...

270
00:18:06,360 --> 00:18:08,660
That's something I'll make happen.

271
00:18:32,920 --> 00:18:34,320
Were you still at the office?

272
00:18:36,150 --> 00:18:37,190
Want to head out together?

273
00:18:53,900 --> 00:18:54,910
We're not...

274
00:18:57,140 --> 00:18:59,040
on those kinds of terms, are we?

275
00:19:00,540 --> 00:19:02,110
Is even that too much to ask?

276
00:19:08,190 --> 00:19:10,190
Can't you see
what I'm trying to do here?

277
00:19:10,820 --> 00:19:13,290
I'm trying to marry Park Hyun Jun.

278
00:19:13,920 --> 00:19:15,390
That's my focus right now.

279
00:19:15,630 --> 00:19:17,630
You still don't look very happy
about it.

280
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:23,400
I can't support you winning this,

281
00:19:23,770 --> 00:19:27,500
but I still want to look out for you
so you don't overdo it.

282
00:19:30,610 --> 00:19:33,580
It's just some warm tea,
so please accept it.

283
00:19:48,630 --> 00:19:54,800
(New Business Task Force Team)

284
00:19:54,930 --> 00:19:55,930
Min Jun.

285
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:01,070
Were you here to see Chloe?

286
00:20:02,510 --> 00:20:03,510
Yes.

287
00:20:04,170 --> 00:20:06,210
I heard about the competition
and I was worried about her.

288
00:20:07,140 --> 00:20:09,150
I told you to let those feelings go.

289
00:20:09,780 --> 00:20:11,520
I've only just realized
how I feel about her.

290
00:20:12,120 --> 00:20:14,050
You're the only one
who'll get hurt in the end.

291
00:20:14,750 --> 00:20:16,720
I survived losing Jin Ju.

292
00:20:18,190 --> 00:20:21,590
Right now, I'm not afraid
of getting hurt again.

293
00:20:26,030 --> 00:20:29,270
I'm not just going to sit by
and watch this competition unfold.

294
00:20:30,830 --> 00:20:33,440
I figured you'd say that.

295
00:20:33,670 --> 00:20:36,610
I'm going to support Chloe
so that she can win.

296
00:20:37,340 --> 00:20:38,380
That's the only way...

297
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:42,950
for you to escape
the marriage you don't want.

298
00:20:43,880 --> 00:20:44,880
I see.

299
00:20:45,250 --> 00:20:48,350
Mother, you can help Chloe,
as you've decided.

300
00:20:49,450 --> 00:20:51,860
As for me, I'll follow my heart.

301
00:21:32,630 --> 00:21:36,370
You'll build the biggest,
most brilliant company?

302
00:21:36,630 --> 00:21:38,640
No. You...

303
00:21:39,440 --> 00:21:42,440
You'll create a nightmare
soaked in blood, you monster.

304
00:21:43,910 --> 00:21:45,240
A monster like you...

305
00:21:45,780 --> 00:21:48,050
dares to covet even more power?

306
00:21:48,550 --> 00:21:50,310
You'll never have it.

307
00:21:50,880 --> 00:21:54,620
You will lose everything
you already possess, you monster!

308
00:22:04,760 --> 00:22:07,260
No!

309
00:22:49,970 --> 00:22:51,880
You're drinking awfully late.

310
00:22:54,410 --> 00:22:56,180
I had a bad dream.

311
00:22:56,850 --> 00:23:00,350
You're just stressed
about the exclusive development rights.

312
00:23:02,750 --> 00:23:05,520
It was supposed to be a done deal.

313
00:23:07,460 --> 00:23:10,360
It would have made me,
Park Tae Ho, untouchable.

314
00:23:11,600 --> 00:23:16,370
I was so close to having power
that would last for decades.

315
00:23:25,210 --> 00:23:26,240
Then,

316
00:23:26,710 --> 00:23:30,210
don't walk away from this deal
for the exclusive development rights.

317
00:23:31,750 --> 00:23:33,180
I'm not the one backing out.

318
00:23:33,250 --> 00:23:37,720
Assemblyman Kwon is,
and that's the problem.

319
00:23:41,020 --> 00:23:44,560
Assemblyman Kwon is a man
driven entirely by greed.

320
00:23:46,530 --> 00:23:48,060
Since he's blinded by greed,

321
00:23:49,170 --> 00:23:51,130
use that to lure him back in.

322
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:55,940
Blinded by greed?

323
00:23:57,170 --> 00:24:00,480
Let's first test how greedy you are.

324
00:24:01,910 --> 00:24:03,310
If doubling it isn't enough,

325
00:24:03,610 --> 00:24:06,450
raise the stakes
and offer him triple.

326
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:09,520
Given your resources,

327
00:24:09,850 --> 00:24:12,820
you should be able to come up
with that kind of money.

328
00:24:17,060 --> 00:24:18,060
Triple?

329
00:24:24,970 --> 00:24:26,370
Triple...

330
00:24:30,670 --> 00:24:33,280
(Adele)

331
00:24:38,920 --> 00:24:40,120
(Consultant, Chloe Lee)

332
00:24:45,320 --> 00:24:47,420
What's she working on
so hard already?

333
00:24:49,290 --> 00:24:52,630
Is she going to betray me
and win instead?

334
00:25:21,890 --> 00:25:24,160
Are you trying
to steal Chloe's work again?

335
00:25:26,460 --> 00:25:28,930
I was just browsing
because there was so much here.

336
00:25:29,500 --> 00:25:31,500
We share an office,
so it should be fine.

337
00:25:31,670 --> 00:25:34,270
That might be someone's work,
not just reference material.

338
00:25:34,470 --> 00:25:35,970
And between competitors,

339
00:25:36,810 --> 00:25:39,580
even a quick peek
can get you in trouble.

340
00:25:40,680 --> 00:25:42,080
If it were that important,

341
00:25:42,080 --> 00:25:43,310
would she just leave it out
like that?

342
00:25:43,710 --> 00:25:45,880
This was obviously meant to be seen.

343
00:25:47,950 --> 00:25:49,750
I was going to drop it,

344
00:25:51,120 --> 00:25:52,560
but you left me no choice.

345
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:02,200
This is Park Min Jun.
We need to tighten...

346
00:26:03,530 --> 00:26:05,000
our internal security.

347
00:26:21,180 --> 00:26:23,590
Are there any problems
with the office CCTV?

348
00:26:23,590 --> 00:26:24,650
No, sir.

349
00:26:26,490 --> 00:26:30,190
We're monitoring it more closely
since the design book was stolen.

350
00:26:31,190 --> 00:26:34,730
Per your instructions,
we're checking restricted areas too.

351
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:38,400
Ms. Chloe, your fingerprint
isn't registered in the system yet.

352
00:26:40,500 --> 00:26:43,610
Please fill out this consent form,
and we'll get you registered.

353
00:26:45,110 --> 00:26:48,750
If I register, will I have to use
my fingerprint every time I enter?

354
00:26:48,810 --> 00:26:51,350
You can get in and out of the office
like you normally do.

355
00:26:51,480 --> 00:26:53,720
This is only for restricted areas...

356
00:26:53,720 --> 00:26:55,450
and as a precaution...

357
00:26:55,620 --> 00:26:59,390
in case of a security issue
like the recent theft.

358
00:27:00,660 --> 00:27:01,790
What a fuss.

359
00:27:02,630 --> 00:27:04,160
Just do it and get it over with.

360
00:27:27,220 --> 00:27:28,250
What's all this?

361
00:27:53,540 --> 00:27:55,850
(Fingerprint Registration Complete)

362
00:28:11,930 --> 00:28:13,200
Did you find anything out?

363
00:28:13,760 --> 00:28:15,830
Is it safe for me
to register my fingerprint?

364
00:28:17,130 --> 00:28:19,940
You won't have much reason
to access the restricted areas,

365
00:28:20,040 --> 00:28:22,970
and they're just storing the prints
for now,

366
00:28:23,110 --> 00:28:24,540
so it shouldn't be a problem
for the time being.

367
00:28:24,840 --> 00:28:27,980
But what if they run a check
on my prints?

368
00:28:28,850 --> 00:28:29,850
Are you worried?

369
00:28:30,280 --> 00:28:31,920
Do you want to alter
the fingerprint data?

370
00:28:32,220 --> 00:28:35,550
Hyun Jun and Min Jun
are constantly suspicious of me.

371
00:28:36,820 --> 00:28:38,890
I don't want to leave
any loose ends.

372
00:28:39,660 --> 00:28:40,960
Please find a way.

373
00:28:42,860 --> 00:28:46,200
A way to resolve this issue?
Let's see.

374
00:29:00,210 --> 00:29:02,110
Persuade Assemblyman Kwon...

375
00:29:03,210 --> 00:29:04,280
to come back.

376
00:29:05,850 --> 00:29:09,320
Tell him
I'll triple the lobbying funds.

377
00:29:11,050 --> 00:29:12,290
I see you've made a decision.

378
00:29:13,320 --> 00:29:16,190
Since you have,
I'll do my best to help, sir.

379
00:29:20,460 --> 00:29:21,900
Park Tae Ho,

380
00:29:22,570 --> 00:29:24,900
I'm going to push you
into a trap of your own greed.

381
00:29:30,470 --> 00:29:32,380
You want to re-register
your fingerprint?

382
00:29:33,210 --> 00:29:35,880
I was at a restricted area,
and the scanner...

383
00:29:36,080 --> 00:29:37,380
couldn't read mine.

384
00:29:38,110 --> 00:29:40,220
I think there might be
an issue with it,

385
00:29:40,620 --> 00:29:42,420
so I should probably register
my fingerprint again.

386
00:29:42,820 --> 00:29:44,990
Really? Just a moment please.

387
00:29:45,260 --> 00:29:46,990
(Employee management: Chloe Lee)

388
00:29:47,060 --> 00:29:48,190
(Status: Awaiting registration)

389
00:29:50,160 --> 00:29:53,560
Hold on,
something looks off over there.

390
00:29:57,930 --> 00:29:59,740
You don't want
to get into trouble for that.

391
00:29:59,740 --> 00:30:01,540
You should look into it first.

392
00:30:02,740 --> 00:30:04,410
All right, please give me a moment.

393
00:30:33,700 --> 00:30:37,040
Delete the existing fingerprint data
and register this one instead.

394
00:30:37,070 --> 00:30:38,210
(Ready to delete)

395
00:30:38,210 --> 00:30:39,340
(Re-registering)

396
00:30:43,580 --> 00:30:45,280
(Re-registering)

397
00:30:57,060 --> 00:30:58,190
(Re-registering)

398
00:30:58,290 --> 00:30:59,860
(Fingerprint Registration Complete)

399
00:31:08,170 --> 00:31:09,870
What were you doing in here?

400
00:31:46,410 --> 00:31:49,410
(Pearl in Red)

401
00:31:49,780 --> 00:31:50,810
Producer Shin?

402
00:31:51,050 --> 00:31:53,450
I need to borrow you for a moment
before your meeting.

403
00:31:53,550 --> 00:31:56,190
The chairman's wife
from the Adele Group is waiting.

404
00:31:56,250 --> 00:31:57,690
Are you two kidding me?

405
00:31:57,850 --> 00:32:01,120
Don't belittle Chloe
or trivialize my feelings for her.

406
00:32:01,260 --> 00:32:05,500
Don't embarrass me in front of her
or Park Min Jun.

407
00:32:05,660 --> 00:32:08,330
You don't get to have it easy,
Choi Yu Na.

408
00:32:08,530 --> 00:32:12,000
It's only fair
that you suffer as much as I have.

409
00:32:12,070 --> 00:32:13,970
Yu Na, my goodness!

410
00:32:15,740 --> 00:32:17,740
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
